==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mephistophelian
<hw>Meph`is*to*phe"li*an</hw></mhw>
<pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>prop. a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
resembling, the devil <persfn>Mephistopheles</persfn>, ⟦ldquo⟧a crafty,
scoffing, relentless fiend;⟦rdquo⟧ devilish in character or aspect;
crafty; showing cunning or ingenuity or wickedness; <as>as, a
<ex>mephistophelean</ex> glint in his eye</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> devilish, diabolic, diabolical,
mephistophelean.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mephistopheles</ent>⟦br⟧
